summary_text: 1. I grew up in a neighborhood. 2. Mrs. Baker was the resident cat lady. 3. She had adopted many cats. 4. I was a tomboy. 5. Mrs. Baker had a young grandson. 6. He tried to befriend me. 7. I didn't take to him. 8. He had poor manners. 9. He left a note saying he was running away. 10. He was upset with Mrs. Baker's nagging. 11. Mrs. Baker came to my treehouse. 12. She brought a big tabby cat. 13. I talked her down. 14. We went to look for her grandson. 15. We found his baseball cap near the old mill. 16. We didn't find him at first. 17. He was hiding in the treehouse. 18. I laid low after the incident. 19. Officer Dawson warned me to stay out of sight.
